main event: One round object, the size of a baseball, was observed flying with a smooth, bright flight path in Wisconsin on 10 May 1956.
interesting points: The object was initially believed to be a meteorite., The object was red in color., The sighting lasted for two minutes., The observation was made using ground radar., The duration of the sighting may have been influenced by the exhaust of a jet aircraft.
witness description: one source who observed the object
